-- Romania Utilities Seek Southern Water, Sewage Network Upgrades
-- B y   I r i n a   S a v u
-- 2012-10-04T13:30:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-04/romania-utilities-seek-southern-water-sewage-network-upgrades.html
Romanian utilities are seeking bids
to upgrade water and sewage infrastructure in the south of the
country for contracts valued at 180.5 million lei ($51 million).  Hidro Prahova SA is waiting for bids until Nov. 27 to award
a 74.5 million-lei contract to extend the sewer network in
Banesti, Campina and Valenii de Munte, according to a European
Union  procurement document  published today. Bidders can also
submit offers until Nov. 26 for a contract valued at 82.4
million lei to upgrade the sewage system in Baicoi, Plopeni and
Urlati, another Hidro Prahova  document  showed.  Apa Service SA, a water utility from Giurgiu county, is
seeking bids until Dec. 3 to expand and upgrade water and sewage
coverage in Bolintin Vale in a 23.6 million-lei contract, a EU
 procurement document  also showed.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Irina Savu in Bucharest at 
 isavu@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
